ğŸ” Real-world analogy:
Minimize max = â€œNo one should be too overloaded.â€

Maximize min = â€œEveryone should get at least some minimum â€” even if one person ends up doing much more.â€

ğŸ’¡ When to use which?
Goal	Use Strategy
Prevent burnout	Minimize the Maximum
Guarantee minimum service	Maximize the Minimum
Equal fairness	Minimize Max + refine via balancing heuristics
Strict quotas / thresholds	Maximize Minimum

ğŸ”‘ Core Binary Search on Answer Strategy:
Step 1: Identify the pattern â€” is it â€œmin of maxâ€ or â€œmax of minâ€?
Step 2: Build a predicate function (isValid()) using greedy logic.
Step 3: Apply binary search on answer space.

ğŸ” Hereâ€™s Your Cheat Framework:
Problem Signal	Type	Search Space	Predicate Logic
â€œMinimize the maximum workload/valueâ€	Min of Max	low = max(arr)
high = sum(arr)	Split when sum > mid
Check if chunks â‰¤ k
â€œMaximize the minimum gap/quota/valueâ€	Max of Min	low = 1 or min(arr)
